{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"Plan-review advisory dispositions (v5 PASS @da7f11fc0, 0 blocking, 17 advisory). Most are consistency notes that F4 (08a8) has now LANDED, so test_release_workflow_pins.py already EXISTS — this story EXTENDS it (not 'introduces'), exactly as the implementation does. ACCEPTED + reflected in implementation:\n- (~0.85 x3) test_release_workflow_pins.py exists (08a8 landed): extend it with the new checks (g) sha256sum -c SHA256SUMS + no-rebuild in publish, (h) wheel-test/sdist-test jobs with named probes, (i) build-once single bundle w/ SHA256SUMS + evidence-artifacts fragment — not just check (f).\n- force_include for sdist: confirmed the hook's build_data['force_include'] in initialize() ships _build_info.py in BOTH wheel + sdist (a test_sdist_ships_build_info test verifies the sdist tarball contains it).\n- hatch_build.py 4-step precedence extracted into a testable helper (_resolve_build_commit) unit-tested for env-wins/preserve/git/None + raise-on-set-but-empty, plus a real REBAR_BUILD_COMMIT=<hex> python -m build E2E asserting the sdist->wheel path bakes the hex (the defect).\nREJECTED: the 0.40 generic 'AC/DoD quality' (vague; ACs are concrete + test-backed after remediation)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784153999419523001,"uuid":"39c5184f-5bec-43d9-bb00-69882c9b41a7"}